   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. % of State Auditors working in the Department for auditing of local self-governments participate in trainings on use of Audit Methodology 
2. Analysis conducted and a debate with key stakeholders held on criteria for definition of audit frequency and scope and to advise SAI further action (yes/no)
3. Number of updates for SCTM e - learning platform on re-occurring external audit findings 
4. Number of meetings with local self-governments and parliamentary committee held with an aim to sensitize stakeholders on common and reoccurring audit findings and identify respective corrective measures; 
5. Working group consisting of State Audit Institution and Ministry of Finance representatives (Central Harmonization Unit-CHU) has developed and implemented its work plan for the joint introduction of internal and external international audit standards (yes/no) 
6. Number of internal municipal auditors received information on international audit standards</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2015">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">Total of 135 audit reports issued so far, 27 of which are municipal audits; The Law on State Audit Institution (SAI) states that SAI should audit &#x201C;an appropriate number of local self-governments on annual basis&#x201D;; Frequency of municipal audits is one in four years</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
